products.title: ARABICA BEANS
products.description: Arabica beans are larger, sweeter, and more expensive than their prime competition, the Robusta.

products.title: ROBUSTA BEANS
products.description: Robusta beans have a lower acidity than Arabica making them less sweet and the type most often used in espresso and in instant coffee.

products.title: BOURBON BEANS
products.description: Bourbon beans are known for their sweet taste with a hint of caramel.

products.title: CATIMOR COFFEE BEANS
products.description: Catimor beans are a hybrid between Caturra & Timor beans which is where their unique name comes from.

products.title: CATURRA COFFEE BEANS
products.description: This combination makes them popular with growers, and the quality coffee they produce makes them popular with roasters.

products.title: GEISHA COFFEE BEANS
products.description: This coffee beans expense is due to the specific conditions required to grow the best beans coupled with the worldwide demand and willingness to pay for the highest quality coffee.

products.title: ICATU COFFEE BEANS
products.description: Icatu beans are a hybrid of a variety of Brazilian beans stemming from both Arabica and Robusta.

products.title: JACKSON COFFEE BEANS
products.description: Mr. Jackson, a coffee planter in India, gave his name to these beans in the early 1900s after he discovered a “new” plant growing on his farm. The natural mutation was found to be resistant to the coffee leaf rust disease that still plagues coffee planters.

products.title: JAMAICAN BLUE MOUNTAIN
products.description: Jamaican Blue Mountain beans are a variety of Arabica beans grown in the Blue Mountains of Jamaica.The beans are known to produce a mild flavor coffee that has made them popular worldwide.

products.title: JAVA COFFEE BEANS
products.description: Java isn’t really a cultivar of coffee but a regional style, but as we have said regional differences in climate, soil, and altitude make a big difference in coffee taste. Java is known as a strong mildly sweet coffee.

products.title: JEMBER COFFEE BEANS
products.description: The beans are said to be sweet with a caramel, brown sugar, or maple flavor.

products.title: KENT COFFEE BEANS
products.description: Kent beans are yet another variety of Typica and thus a subvariety of Arabica. They are native to India where they were discovered in the early 20th Century as a natural mutation of Typica.

products.title: KONA COFFEE BEANS
products.description: Kona Beans are grown on Hawaii’s Big Island on the slopes of Hualalai and Mauna Loa in the Kona District.

products.title: LIBERICA COFFEE BEANS
products.description: The taste of these beans is known to be rather inconsistent which limits worldwide popularity.

products.title: MARAGATURA COFFEE BEANS
products.description: They are a high yielding plant, but the beans require a lot of maintenance. They are said to produce a fine cup of Joe

products.title: MARAGOGYPE COFFEE BEANS
products.description: . The taste of this coffee varies widely depending on where it is grown in Brazil and the quality of soil on each farm or plantation.

products.title: MOCHA COFFEE BEANS
products.description: These small, oddly shaped, yellow beans do, however, have a mildly chocolaty taste, combined with Java beans brought by traders on the Silk Road. This combination appears to be largely lost to posterity and the innumerable variations in coffee beans and coffee drinks.

products.title: MUNDO NOVO COFFEE BEANS
products.description: The plants are highly productive, but also disease prone which keeps them from a higher level of cultivation.

products.title: PACAMARA COFFEE BEANS
products.description: This coffee bean type demonstrates how in the wide world of coffee all beans really trace their origin back to Arabica and Robusta plants through a variety of mutations and hybridizations.

products.title: PACAS COFFEE BEANS
products.description: This variety has not taken off in popularity or production as it is more prone to disease damage than some other varieties and produces a coffee generally rated good but not great.
